def plot_df(df, x, y, title="Set and Room temp", xlabel='Datetime', ylabel='Temperature', dpi=100):
    plt.figure(figsize=(16,5), dpi=dpi)
    plt.plot(x, y)
    plt.gca().set(title=title, xlabel=xlabel, ylabel=ylabel)
    plt.show()

plot_df(df, x=df.index, y=df[['Room_temp', 'Set_temp']] )

df_new = pd.read_csv(r"C:\Users\admin\novo\new_data_csv\working_data\cleaned_4.csv", parse_dates=True, infer_datetime_format=True)

#solving error for horizontal lines plotting in line charts
df_new.Datetime = pd.to_datetime(df_new['Datetime'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')
df_new.sort_values('Datetime', inplace=True)


df_new['month'] = [d.strftime('%m') for d in df_new.Datetime]
years = df_new['Year'].unique()


# Draw Plot
fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,2, figsize=(20,7), dpi= 80)
sns.boxplot(x='Year', y='Room_temp', data=df_new, ax=axes[0])
sns.boxplot(x='month', y='Room_temp', data=df_new)

# Set Title
axes[0].set_title('Year-wise Box Plot\n(The Trend)', fontsize=18); 
axes[1].set_title('Month-wise Box Plot\n(The Seasonality)', fontsize=18)
plt.show()

In [21]:
from statsmodels.tsa.seasonal import seasonal_decompose
from dateutil.parser import parse


# Multiplicative Decomposition 
result_mul = seasonal_decompose(df['Room_temp'], model='multiplicative', extrapolate_trend='freq',freq=1000)

# Additive Decomposition
result_add = seasonal_decompose(df['Room_temp'], model='additive', extrapolate_trend='freq',freq=365)

# Plot
plt.rcParams.update({'figure.figsize': (16,10)})
result_mul.plot().suptitle('Multiplicative Decompose', fontsize=22)
result_add.plot().suptitle('Additive Decompose', fontsize=22)
plt.show()

from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss

# ADF Test
#if test statistic < critical value shown then time series is stationary
#if p-value > significance level of 0.05 and test statistic > any critical value, time series is non-stationary

#time-series data is stationary

series = df.loc[:, 'Room_temp'].values

result = adfuller(series, autolag='AIC')
print(f'ADF Statistic: {result[0]}')
print(f'n_lags: {result[1]}')
print(f'p-value: {result[1]}')
for key, value in result[4].items():
    print('Critial Values:')
    print(f'   {key}, {value}')   

ADF Statistic: -21.40158295547457
n_lags: 0.0
p-value: 0.0
Critial Values:
   1%, -3.4303657357579262
Critial Values:
